From VEAL David Veal Subject Re AMA Support Brady Bill In article Daryl Biberdorf writes The following was sent to me by a friend of mine a med student It originally appeared in a medical discussion GUN CONTROL The AMA expressed support for and the Brady Handgun Violence Prevention Act Citing its strong support for the Brady Bill in past Congresses the AMA termed as particularly alarming violence associated with and stemming from the widespread and easy availability and use of The AMA proceeded to comment While we recognize that a waiting period of business days before a handgun purchase will not address all of the difficult problems that have made violence so prevalent in our society we believe that it is a beginning and will save Physicians are first hand witnesses to the horrendous cost in human life being exacted by firearm A reasonable waiting period before the purchase of a handgun is a protection that the American people Letters to Senator Howard Metzenbaum and Representative Charles Schumer March I wonder if the AMA has an exact listing of lives saved in Tennessee California and other waiting period David Veal of of Education Services Group PA I still remember the way you laughed the day your pushed me down the elevator shaft I'm beginning to think you don't love me Weird Al